cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of heterogeneous networks (HetNets) in LTE-A, which is a networking and internet architecture topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives outage probability, rate coverage probability, and mean user bit-rate, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel prioritized SIR-based cell association scheme, which can be considered as a system and control topic. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the mean user bit-rate, which is related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed scheme and provides insights for network operators, which is related to performance evaluation.
